Comment: Saragossa opening (A00). I wasn't at all familiar with that opening.
I felt d5 was the best response.
Odd move to me, but since c3 is occupied deliberately perhaps there is a plan I can't see yet.
I continue to develop as usual.
Push for center control.
Looking back I'm not sure this was the best choice. I wanted to get control of the diagonal and didn't dare move e5 but perhaps I could have been more patient with it.
I think there was an early plan to defend d4 with a knight at c2.
I chose to develop as usual.
Knight pin.
Now that I have my Knight in place to capture back I challenge the d4 pawn. I lost tempo here I suppose.
dxe5 as expected.
I felt that I gained space after the exchange and was happy to open up another diagonal in an area controlled by my Knights.
Protects against a likely Bg4.
Starting to put pressure on f2. I expect an eventual 0-0 if Bxf6...Qxf6 I'll be in a good position.
White realizes the weakness and advances and additionally threatens my Knight although potentially weakens the pawn.
I felt this would be a good spot for my Knight and I liked the control I had over e3.
Chases away my Knight.

I am forcing a trade of Knights. To some degree it seems silly to have my Knight chased around just to trade it away but I really liked my Bishop on e3. I figured I could defend it well and it would cramp the King and make it difficult to maneuver.
Nxe3 as expected.
I like the control here and like the possibility of potentially snagging a free pawn.
